Day 116 of asking /matcha to support limit orders on /base 

IN PERSON MODE ENABLED at /ethdenver 

At the ETHDenver Afterparty, YES2Crypto (barefoot, armed only with a cold wallet) sneaks into Nakatoshi DEX after /matcha mercenaries seize the roadmap, demanding ‚Äú100 ETH in bribes or limit orders stay locked.‚Äù

"You brought a meme campaign‚Ä¶ to a fee-war" sneers Hans Rugger, his eyes flickering with profit-maximizing algo trades. "Did you really think JPEGs and raindrops could outdo my intelligent routing and low fees?"

Dodging FUD grenades and rug pull charges, YES2Crypto shimmies through liquidity vents, grinning:

‚ÄúYippee-ki-yay, roadmap delay.‚Äù

Hans Rugger sneers: ‚ÄúThis time, the memers do not walk off into the sunset with PMF‚Äù

YES2Crypto responds: "That's limit orders, gas whole"

Hans: "AAAAAHGHGHGHGGHGHGH"

But YES2Crypto, hardened by rug pulls and armed with a top hat of defiance, rallies degens at the Tech Noir mempool. 

‚ÄúI‚ÄôLL BE BACK,‚Äù glitches the /matcha-T800, its red-eyed UI flickering as YES2Crypto jams a hardware wallet into its transaction queue. 

Meanwhile, a grizzled Vitalik-bot whispers: ‚ÄúThe future remains unwritten‚Ä¶ unless you deploy on a Stage 2 L2.‚Äù

text:
Spent much more time this year at /ethdenver with Farcasters and enjoyed every moment. Can‚Äôt wait for /farcon-nyc! 

For those who:
üíúare on the waitlist, please be patient with the team. As they see if people claim their tix, more spots may open 

üíúcan‚Äôt attend because of cost or travel challenges? Spin up your own FarAwayCon like they did in Europe last year or FarCon Asia. Doesn‚Äôt have to be a full blown conference. 

üíúplan your own side event like /nouns is doing leading up to or after FarCon

üíúor take the initiative to do your own full blown FarCon of your own like /farconasia 

There‚Äôs lots of folks who missed the application process for many reasons. And space is limited. This isn‚Äôt meant to be a huge festival like Eth Denver. It‚Äôs a summit of builders. 

So if you don‚Äôt agree with the decisions of the VOLUNTEERS putting together this event, take initiative and create your own. Literally no one is stopping you.

text:
‚ú® FAQ: So You Got A Weird Token In Your Warpcast Wallet ‚ú® 

Warpcast Wallet hides spammy tokens by default, but you may notice unknown tokens listed if you choose to tap "Show All." These are almost always spam or scams. And once in a while a spammy token makes it past the filter. These tokens will usually try to trick you into visiting a malicious website by displaying a link in the token name or in an error message.

The best and safest thing you can do is to IGNORE THEM. Just don't interact at all.

Q: I got an unknown token. What should I do with it?
A: Ignore it.

Q: It says it's an airdrop. Is this free money?
A: No, ignore it. This is a scam.

Q: Should I send it out of my wallet?
A: No, ignore it.

Q: Should I swap it for another token?
A: No, ignore it.

Q: There's a website in the token name, should I visit it?
A: No, ignore it. The link is a scam.

Q: I tried to swap it and the error says to go to a website. Should I visit it?
A: No, ignore it. The link is a scam.

How to verify your frame to earn weekly rewards:

1. Turn on developer mode in the mobile app
2. Go to Settings > Developer > Domains
3. Enter your full frame domain. Don‚Äôt include ‚Äúhttps‚Äù.
4. Copy the generated manifest, fill in the blanks, and serve it at .well-known/farcaster.json
5. Tap ‚Äúcheck domain status‚Äù in the dev tools to verify it.
6. When you change it, tap ‚Äúcheck domain status‚Äù again to refresh it and re-verify it.
7. Earn weekly frame developer rewards.

Base Colors ü§ù  Warpcast Rewards Leaderboard

If you finished in the Top 100 on the Warpcast Rewards Leaderboard last week, you just received a 1/1 color as a reward. Straight to your Warplet.

Launch the Base Colors frame below to view your color and hit the pencil to give it a 1/1 name. https://frame.basecolors.com
